The article discusses the swearing-in of a new Supreme Court justice named Judge Jackson, who has now become Justice Jackson. The author expresses their honor and pride in selecting Judge Jackson as their first judicial nominee as President. They emphasize the significance of having a young, Black woman on the highest court and how it represents progress for the nation. Justice Jackson is praised for her intellect, temperament, and credentials as a former public defender and district and circuit judge. Her nomination received bipartisan support and endorsement from legal experts and law enforcement organizations. Justice Jackson's background as the daughter of educators and niece of a police chief, as well as her dedication to public service, is highlighted. The author believes that Justice Jackson's wisdom and experience will make the nation proud for many years to come. They also express gratitude to Justice Steven Breyer, whom Justice Jackson succeeds, for his years of service and commitment to the country.